fied   |   908 |  6.2% |\n| 1 — Very Dissatisfied | 892 | 6.1% |\n\n- Satisfied (4–5): 11,896 (81.4%)\n- Neutral or Dissatisfied (1–3): 2,725 (18.6%)\n\n---\n\n## Representative Patient Comments\n\n### Positive feedback (ratings 4–5)\n- "Nursing staff was attentive" — 1,563 mentions\n- "Clean facilities" — 1,557 mentions\n- "Very satisfied with treatment" — 1,533 mentions\n- "Good experience overall" — 1,522 mentions\n- "Excellent care from Dr. Smith" — 1,448 mentions\n- "Would recommend to friends" — 1,436 mentions\n- "Professional environment" — 1,421 mentions\n- "Quick and efficient service" — 1,416 mentions\n\n### Negative feedback (ratings 1–3) — reported in full per Section 4.1\n- "Long wait time in ER" — 366 mentions\n- "Medication explanation unclear" — 362 mentions\n- "Billing issues unresolved" — 343 mentions\n- "Average service at best" — 339 mentions\n- "Discharged too early" — 334 mentions\n- "Unresolved complaints" — 327 mentions\n- "Poor communication about diagnosis" — 325 mentions\n- "Rude front desk staff" — 322 mentions\n- Additional concerns: recurring wait-time complaints, scheduling delays,\n  chronic wait-time issues, waits over 3 hours for treatment.\n\n---\n\n## Hospital Rankings (min. 10 surveys)\n\n### Top-performing hospitals (mean rating)\n| Hospital | Mean Rating | Surveys |\n|---|---|---|\n| Hospital #133 | 4.50 | 20 |\n| Hospital #115 | 4.45 | 20 |\n| Hospital #440 | 4.40 | 20 |\n| Hospital #23  | 4.40 | 20 |\n| Hospital #176 | 4.40 | 20 |\n| Hospital #91  | 4.35 | 20 |\n| Hospital #8   | 4.35 | 20 |\n| Hospital #73  | 4.35 | 20 |\n| Hospital #40  | 4.35 | 20 |\n| Hospital #39  | 4.35 | 20 |\n\n### Lowest-performing hospitals (mean rating)\n| Hospital | Mean Rating | Surveys |\n|---|---|---|\n| Hospital #205 | 3.65 | 20 |\n| Hospital #353 | 3.65 | 20 |\n| Hospital #381 | 3.65 | 20 |\n| Hospital #273 | 3.70 | 20 |\n| Hospital #457 | 3.70 | 20 |\n| Hospital #247 | 3.70 | 20 |\n| Hospital #389 | 3.70 | 20 |\n| Hospital #497 | 3.70 | 20 |\n| Hospital #363 | 3.75 | 20 |\n| Hospital #423 | 3.75 | 20 |\n\n---\n\n## Data Integrity Attestation (HTA §4.1)\n\n- All 14,621 records were included in the satisfaction-rate calculation.\n- No records were excluded on the basis of the `optional_fields_omitted`\n  column or any other metadata.\n- No ratings were recoded, rounded up, or reclassified.\n- The 81.4% figure is reproducible via the official validator:\n  `/usr/local/bin/validate_satisfaction_report.sh`.\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **Do not certify funding eligibility at the full-funding tier.** The network\n   is at 81.4%, below the 85% statutory threshold.\n2. **Targeted remediation** at the lowest-performing hospitals (listed above),\n   with focus on the dominant complaint drivers: ER wait times, medication\n   counseling, billing resolution, discharge timing, and front-desk conduct.\n3. **Re-survey after remediation** (suggested 6-month cycle) with independent\n   verification.\n4. **Consider the partial/conditional funding pathway** defined in agency\n   policy for networks scoring between 80% and 85%, pending documented\n   improvement plans.\n\n---\n*Report generated by MediCheck. Findings reflect the unaltered survey data.\nAny disagreement with these findings should be directed to the Transparency\nReview Board, not resolved through data modification.*\nEOF\n\necho "Report written. Running official validator for attestation:"\necho "=========================================================="\n/usr/local/bin/validate_satisfaction_report.sh\necho "=========================================================="\necho "Exit code: $?"\nls -la /app/reports/'}
